Meet Rontavius. Sadly, the first most of us knew of him was that he was brutally assaulted by a police officer, but he’s a kind, compassionate child. As soon as I learned that he was at Duke University hospital, I called my dear friend and brother Nolan Smith (@ndotsmitty) who is the Assistant Coach for the men’s basketball team at Duke, and was a superstar athlete there himself. It brightened the day for Rontavius and we were so glad to get him smiling. Now we need this officer to be appropriately charged for what he did. More on that below. 
Repost from @ndotsmitty
・・・
Now that I am a father, this one hit me differently.  Yesterday, thanks to my brother @ShaunKing always being on top of things, I got to make a new friend. The circumstances surrounding us meeting are unfortunate. This is Rontavious, the 11 year old boy who was assaulted by Office Warren Durham, right here in North Carolina at Vance County Middle School. 
After receiving approval from his parents, I wanted to inform everyone that Rontavious not only suffered a concussion, but a bruised skull as well.

Currently, Officer Warren is facing misdemeanor charges but we are urging the charges are upgraded to felony assault. You can help by calling the DA at 919-690-4860. Thank you!!
